report on Haiti And,

00:27:06.150 --> 00:27:10.260
because I helped her
proofread it I got a basic.

00:27:10.260 --> 00:27:11.560 position:56%
&gt;&gt; Edwidge Danticat: Just proofread?

00:27:11.560 --> 00:27:14.150
&gt;&gt; Well yeah, well I got
a basic understanding

00:27:14.150 --> 00:27:15.910
or an education on Haiti.

00:27:15.910 --> 00:27:19.590
And, a lot of times, when
we don't live other places,

00:27:19.590 --> 00:27:22.000
we're just concerned
about where we are.

00:27:22.000 --> 00:27:24.480
One of the things that I
found a lot of interest

00:27:24.480 --> 00:27:29.460
in was Haiti is a predominantly
black country.

00:27:29.460 --> 00:27:32.100
But, they have a color issue.

00:27:32.100 --> 00:27:35.990
So, you know, they go by the
whites, light skin, dark skin.

00:27:35.990 --> 00:27:42.320
Had you ever thought about
doing a book about that issue?

00:27:42.320 --> 00:27:43.620
&gt;&gt; Edwidge Danticat: Well, I mean,

00:27:43.620 --> 00:27:46.410
color is certainly
not unique to Haiti.

00:27:46.410 --> 00:27:52.770 position:56%
It's a, so, if you imagine, see like
in Brazil and Haiti and other places

00:27:52.770 --> 00:27:54.300
where we had colonialism

00:27:54.300 --> 00:27:58.570
and in Hattie we had the
French as the Colonial power.

00:27:58.570 --> 00:28:01.900
And there was, there was a
chart, there was something

00:28:01.900 --> 00:28:08.690
like 300 racial categories,
right, that was just like,

00:28:08.690 --> 00:28:12.730
so they were saying if you were a
mulatto, had a kid with an accent,

00:28:12.730 --> 00:28:17.260
like the whole, I mean it
was like an insane chart of,

00:28:17.260 --> 00:28:21.210
and then of course, the higher,
the lighter you were on that,

00:28:21.210 --> 00:28:24.580
in that chart, the more privileges
you had, because you know,

00:28:24.580 --> 00:28:27.670
some of the children of the,

00:28:27.670 --> 00:28:32.470
of the owners of the enslaved
people would then send their kids

00:28:32.470 --> 00:28:35.770
to friends, and then there's
a very interesting case.

00:28:35.770 --> 00:28:38.670
There's a novel that's about to
come out by Marie Vieux-Chauvet,

00:28:38.670 --> 00:28:43.480
