jewelry, like their diamonds,

00:28:50.920 --> 00:28:54.800
they were like the
mistresses of these rich guys

00:28:54.800 --> 00:28:57.660
and they gave them jewels, and
they weren't allowed to wear them

00:28:57.660 --> 00:29:00.210
on their, so they would
wear these loop earrings,

00:29:00.210 --> 00:29:02.060
or they would wear their
diamonds on their toes.

00:29:02.060 --> 00:29:05.030
You know, they would find
ways to like define the thing.

00:29:05.030 --> 00:29:10.350
So I think, just as it is in this
country, color is, I mean, it's so,

00:29:10.350 --> 00:29:14.700
it's part of, it's a part of
white supremacy that's very hard

00:29:14.700 --> 00:29:16.570
to extract.

00:29:16.570 --> 00:29:22.210 position:56%
So I, I feel like, I mean it's not a
story that I want to concentrate on,

00:29:22.210 --> 00:29:24.390
because I don't think
it's unique to us.

00:29:24.390 --> 00:29:27.510
I mean, maybe in part of it,
sort of it's allowed with power,

00:29:27.510 --> 00:29:31.010
it's allowed with money from
the whole colonial period.

00:29:31.010 --> 00:29:33.140
And so it's something
that is definitely one

00:29:33.140 --> 00:29:35.230
of the ills we suffered from.

00:29:35.230 --> 00:29:38.150
But I think it's also
buffered in a place like Haiti,

00:29:38.150 --> 00:29:41.080
by the fact that you have
a majority black population

00:29:41.080 --> 00:29:43.570
and you have dark skin
presidents and you have, you know,

00:29:43.570 --> 00:29:46.140
you've seen all these variations.

00:29:46.140 --> 00:29:51.460
But if I, wherever it's written,
if I, I would love to read a book

00:29:51.460 --> 00:29:54.270
on it, whether it's about
the US or about Brazil,

00:29:54.270 --> 00:29:56.530 position:56%
but that gives me more than we know.

00:29:56.530 --> 00:29:59.880
You know? And for me, like, I
don't feel like I have that passion

00:29:59.880 --> 00:30:04.730
